Now I can see the vulnerable code. The function `nas_proc_get_loc_info()` at line 544 uses `sprintf()` without bounds checking to format TAC and CI values into caller-provided buffers. Let me fix this by replacing `sprintf()` with `snprintf()` and adding the appropriate size limits.

According to the PR description:
- TAC buffer needs 5 bytes (4 hex digits + null terminator)
- CI buffer needs 9 bytes (8 hex digits + null terminator)

